quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  46,6,"When such people are gathered, they will become their enemies and will reject their worship.",""
  46,7,"When Our clear verses are recited to them, those who disbelieve say about the truth when it comes to them, “This is clear magic.”",""
  46,8,"Or do they say, “He has fabricated it”? Say, “If I did fabricate it, there is nothing you can do to protect me against Allah. He knows best that in which you indulge<sup>2</sup>. He is Sufficient as a witness between me and you, and He is the All-Forgiving, the Most Merciful.”","[2] Of false accusations and slander about Qu’ran and Prophet (ﷺ)."
  46,9,"Say, “I am not the first of the messengers<sup>3</sup>, nor do I know what will happen to me or to you. I only follow what is revealed to me, and I am not but a clear warner.”","[3] To be surprised at my message, nor have I brought something different from the previous messengers."
  46,10,"Say, “What do you think, if this [Qur’an] is really from Allah and yet you reject it, and a witness<sup>4</sup> from the Children of Israel has testified in its favor and believed<sup>5</sup>, whereas you persist in arrogance<sup>6</sup>? Indeed, Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people.”","[4] Such as Abdullah ibn Salām, a Jewish scholar, who accepted Islam when the Prophet (ﷺ) emigrated from Makkah to Medina.\n [5] Based on information in the Torah testifying his message.\n [6] The estimated conclusion could be ""...would you not then be unjust and wrongdoer people?"""
  46,11,"The disbelievers say about the believers, “If this [faith] were something good, they<sup>7</sup> would not have believed in it before us.” Now since they are not guided by it, they will say, “This is an old fabrication.”","[7] These poor and powerless individuals and slaves who embraced Islam."
  46,12,"And before it was the Scripture of Moses a guide and a mercy. This Book is a confirmation of it, in the Arabic language, in order to warn those who do wrong and give glad tidings to those who do good.",""
  46,13,"Indeed, those who say, “Our Lord is Allah”, then remain steadfast, they will have no fear, nor will they grieve.",""
  46,14,"They are the people of Paradise; abiding therein forever, as a reward for what they used to do.",""
